============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/12-0b9bd80/improvement-plan.md`.

**Summary of the plan:**

The 17 failures all stem from two gaps in candidate filtering — no bullet-line detection and incomplete ingredient/section-label recognition. Four changes fix them:

1. **Bullet-line filter** (`/^\s*[-•*]\s/` in `passesHardFilters`) — eliminates all 16 bullet-prefixed failures at the source. Single regex, zero risk.

2. **Section label filter** (blocklist: `INGREDIENTS`, `SKŁADNIKI`, `DIRECTIONS`, etc.) — fixes Mozzarella Sticks where `INGREDIENTS` was promoted over the real title. Also defense-in-depth for Polish documents with `SKŁADNIKI` first.

3. **Expanded ingredient detection** — Polish units (`łyżka`, `szklanka`, `szczypta`), compact metrics (`100g`, `50ml`), and "to taste"/"do smaku" patterns. Backup for cookbooks that don't use bullet markers.

4. **`startsWithNumber` hardening** (optional) — catch digits after bullet markers. Fully redundant with Change 1, included only as a safety net.

All changes are additive filters — no scoring, threshold, or dedup logic is touched. Zero additional embedding calls. No regression risk to the 80+ passing tests.
