{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013HmAY21J55nxHXbAsEetDW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding. Let me outline my approach before writing the plan.\n\n**Key proposed changes:**\n\n1. **Bullet-line filter (fixes Pattern 1 + Pattern 3):** Lines starting with `- ` or `• ` are structural markers for list items (ingredients/instructions). Adding a single regex check in `passesHardFilters` eliminates all 12 ingredient-bullet failures and all 4 compound-join failures at the source — these candidates never enter the pool.\n\n2. **Known section label filter (fixes Pattern 2):** Words like `INGREDIENTS`, `SKŁADNIKI`, `DIRECTIONS`, `PRZYGOTOWANIE` are section headers, never recipe titles. Adding them to a blocklist in `passesHardFilters` prevents `INGREDIENTS` from winning in the Mozzarella Sticks case, and also fixes the `isSubHeader` mis-trigger by removing SKŁADNIKI/INGREDIENTS before scoring.\n\n3. **Expanded ingredient detection (defense-in-depth):** Polish measurement units (`łyżka`, `szklanka`, `szczypta`), compact metrics (`\\b\\d+g\\b`, `\\b\\d+ml\\b`), and \"to taste\"/\"do smaku\" patterns round out `looksLikeIngredient` to catch edge cases the bullet filter might miss.\n\n4. **Fix `isSubHeader` to check if `sortedCaps[0]` is a section label:** When the first ALL_CAPS heading is a section label (now caught by the filter above), it shouldn't be promoted as the title. This is defense-in-depth for documents where section labels survive filtering."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":655,"cache_read_input_tokens":48796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":655},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"866f68b5-3ea0-400d-9a2a-138f41106e3f","uuid":"f3b8cd46-65e4-4ac0-8d37-84f81c486874"}
